Ahold, Alfacam, Belgacom, RHJ, Solvay: Benelux Equity Preview

-- B y   J o h n   M a r t e n s
-- 
2011-07-01T04:00:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/ahold-alfacam-belgacom-rhj-solvay-benelux-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Benelux markets. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are from the previous close.  The  AEX-Index (AEX)  in Amsterdam advanced 1.3 percent to 339.65.
Belgium’s Bel20 Index rose 1 percent to 2,572.58. Luxembourg’s
LuxX Index gained 0.7 percent to 1,406.91.  Dutch stocks:  Royal Ahold NV (AH NA): The Dutch owner of Stop & Shop
supermarkets in the U.S. named James McCann as its chief
commercial and development officer starting Sept. 1. McCann left
Carrefour in May after little more than a year in charge of the
French retailer’s domestic unit. Ahold shares climbed 0.4
percent to 9.27 euros.  Belgian stocks:  Alfacam Group (ALFA)  NV: The owner of Europe’s largest
fleet of high-definition broadcast trucks said its second-
quarter performance won’t make up for a “weak” first quarter
and forecast a “substantially better” second half. Alfacam
also named Sven Marinus as its chief operating officer. The
shares last traded for 4.68 euros on June 29.  Belgacom SA (BELG)  : The biggest telephone company in
Belgium said it sold the Spanish subsidiary of its Telindus
Group NV unit to funds advised and managed by Corpfin Capital.
Terms of the transaction weren’t disclosed. Belgacom increased 1
percent to 24.60 euros.  RHJ International (RHJI)  SA: The owner of U.K. wealth
manager Kleinwort Benson completed the sale of its 77.9 percent
holding in Niles Co., a maker of switches and other electronic
components for carmakers including Nissan Motor Co., to Valeo SA
(FR FP) for 15.4 billion yen ($190 million) in cash. RHJ was
unchanged at 4.97 euros.  Solvay SA (SOLB)  : The world’s largest soda-ash maker
said it notified the European Commission of its planned purchase
of Rhodia SA (RHA FP) in order to get antitrust approval for the
transaction. Solvay retreated 0.1 percent to 106.55 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
